###Block: Darnoc abilities
# Ability Name		Unique Key					Category of Ability		Type								Define					Description																																																																																																			Modify VAR							Source Page
Create Spawn		KEY:Create Spawn ~ Darnoc		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural									DESC:Any humanoid slain by a darnoc becomes a darnoc in 1d4 rounds. Spawn are under the command of the darnoc that created them and remain enslaved until its death. They do not possess any of the abilities they had in life.																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.144
Curse of the Grave	KEY:Curse of the Grave ~ Darnoc	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural									DESC:Any damage dealt by a darnoc's slam attack does not heal naturally and resists all magical healing (potions, cure spells, and so on). Before the damage can be healed, the curse must first be broken with a Break Enchantment or Remove Curse spell (requiring a DC 20 caster level check for either spell).																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.144
Ghost Form			KEY:Ghost Form ~ Darnoc			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.Defensive							DESC:As a standard action, a darnoc can become incorporeal for up to 10 minutes each day. While incorporeal, the darnoc has loses its natural armor bonus but gains a +%1 deflection bonus and can use its slam attack as an incorporeal touch against corporeal targets dealing 1d6 points of negative energy damage as well as curse of the grave.|max(1,CHA)																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.144
Symbol of Discord		KEY:Symbol of Discord ~ Darnoc	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural			DEFINE:DarnocSymbolOfDiscordDC|0	DESC:Once per day as a standard action, a darnoc can scribe a symbol in the air. All creatures with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher within 60 feet who see the symbol must succeed on a DC %1 Will save or immediately fall into loud bickering and arguing. Meaningful communication is impossible. If the affected creatures have different alignments, there is a 50%% chance that they attack each other. Bickering lasts 5d4 rounds. Fighting begins 1d4 rounds into the bickering and lasts 2d4 rounds. Once triggered, the symbol lasts 2 hours. This is a mind-affecting effect.|DarnocSymbolOfDiscordDC	BONUS:VAR|DarnocSymbolOfDiscordDC|10+(HD/2)+CHA	SOURCEPAGE:p.144

###Block: Demon (Alu-Demon) abilities
# Ability Name	Unique Key					Category of Ability		Type						Description																																																Source Page
Vampiric Touch	KEY:Vampiric Touch ~ Alu-Demon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:An alu-demon gains temporary hit points equal to the damage dealt each time she successfully hits with a claw attack. She cannot gain more than her target's current hit points + the target's Con score (which is enough to kill the target). The temporary hit points disappear in one hour.	SOURCEPAGE:p.154

###Block: Eye of the Deep abilities
# Ability Name	Unique Key						Category of Ability		Type						Define							Description																																																																																																																																																																				Modify VAR																			Source Page		Aspects
Eye Rays		KEY:Eye Rays ~ Eye of the Deep		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DEFINE:EyeOfTheDeepEyeRaysDC|10+(HD/2)+CON	DESC:Each of the creature's eyes stalks can produce a magical ray once per round as a free action. The creature can aim both of its eye rays in any direction. Each of its eye rays resembles a spell cast by a 12th-level caster and follows the rules for a ray. Each eye ray has a range of 150 feet and a save DC of %1. Hold Person: left eye — a target struck by this ray must succeed on a Will save or be affected as though by the spell. An eye of the deep will use this ray early in a fight so as to disable its opponents. Hold Monster: right eye — a target struck by this ray must succeed on a Will save or be affected as though by the spell. This is used in the same manner as the hold person ray. Minor Image: by combining the rays of both eyes, the eye of the deep can replicate the Minor Image spell. It does not have to succeed on an attack roll to use this ray. The illusion is generated at any point within range and in the eye of the deep's line of sight.|EyeOfTheDeepEyeRaysDC	BONUS:VAR|EyeOfTheDeepEyeRaysDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Eye Rays)									SOURCEPAGE:p.275	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(DC %1)|EyeOfTheDeepEyeRaysDC
Stun Cone		KEY:Stun Cone ~ Eye of the Deep		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DEFINE:EyeOfTheDeepStunConeDC|0			DESC:An eye of the deep's central eye can, once per round, produce a cone extending straight ahead from its front to a range of 30 feet. Creatures in the area must succeed on a DC %1 Fortitude save or be stunned for 2d4 rounds.|EyeOfTheDeepStunConeDC																																																																																																																												BONUS:VAR|EyeOfTheDeepStunConeDC|10+(HD/2)+CON	BONUS:VAR|EyeOfTheDeepStunConeDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Stun Cone)	SOURCEPAGE:p.275	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(30-ft. cone, DC %1, stunned 2d4 rounds)|EyeOfTheDeepStunConeDC
Swim-By Attack	KEY:Swim-By Attack ~ Eye of the Deep	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary									DESC:An eye of the deep's Flyby Attack feat allows it to take a move action and another standard action at any point during the move while swimming. It cannot take a second move action during a round in which it makes a flyby attack.																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.275

